TEHRAN, Nov. 17 (Xinhua) -- An explosion took place in Maroon-5 gas transmission line in Ramshir county in southwestern Iran on Wednesday, official IRNA news agency reported. Deputy Governor of Ramshir County Jalil Zahiri told IRNA that the explosion, which was followed by a fire in the pipeline, did not result in casualties of inhabitants of the nearby village of Ramis. The worn-out condition of the pipeline was the cause of blast, said Zahiri, adding that the fire has been contained. "This is the second explosion in this transmission line in the past month, and it is necessary for the oil company to take necessary measures as soon as possible to prevent other accidents," he noted. The extent of damage to the transmission facilities is not yet known, he added. Maroon-5 Oil and Gas Company, which is located in Ramshir county, is affiliated to Ahwaz Maroon Oil and Gas Exploitation Company in southwestern Iran. Enditem